      "raw_text": "In reference to freight and passen-\nger rates ]. ]. Hill stated in an in\nterview yesterday that he would make\nno changes unless compelled to do\nSO. He expressed pleasure over the\nlarge wheat crop in this section and\nthe high prices realized by the farm\ners, and said that was one of the\nbest indications of prosperous coun-\ntry. Mr.. Hill left in his special train\nfor the east about 5 o'clock."
